</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I spent Tuesday and Wednesday there, and moder=
ated a panel on ENERGY. The whole conference was, if you&#8217;ll excuse th=
e pun, electric. The timing was coincidental, but it was the perfect way to=
 spend the Weekly Dose of Optimism&#8217;s 100th week. </p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>A little over two years ago, feeling the heavy deep mid-2022 pessim=
ism, I wrote a post titled </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/=
7e7c7e96-17fb-4d53-8e54-c6bf7a646fa7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-dec=
oration: underline;">Optimism</a><span>, in which I said that Not Boring&#8=
217;s mission is to make the world more optimistic and made the case for op=
timism in three parts: </span></p><ol style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">=
<li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-=
bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>We&#8217;re more pessimistic than we=
 should be.</strong></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=
=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Optim=
ism shapes reality.</strong></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p=
 style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong=
>The downside to optimism is limited, the upside is uncapped.</strong></p><=
/li></ol><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Part of the reason for the pessimism was t=
hat the press serves up the most negative stories it can find, and takes th=
e most negative angle on even the most positive stories. The view from my d=
ay job(s) &#8212; writing this newsletter and investing at Not Boring Capit=
al &#8212; was completely different. Every day, I meet people doing things =
that seem straight out of the pages of utopian </span><a href=3D"https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/24f34fde-4874-4d51-bd3f-c607848aa7d5?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">sci-fi</a><span>. Entrepreneurs, s=
cientists, researchers, and all sorts of people are producing clean, abunda=
nt energy, curing cancer, giving hearing back to deaf kids, launching huge =
rockets into space, landing them back on earth, and building machines that =
can think. They&#8217;re fighting &#8212; and often winning &#8212; to make=
 the world a better place. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But you would=
n&#8217;t know it if you opened up a newspaper or a popular website. So a m=
onth later, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/507ad794-fd1d-4=
7b2-a054-4435c57f4775?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underl=
ine;">Dan</a><span> and I started writing the </span><a href=3D"https://sub=
stack.com/redirect/3787b252-d76f-4029-81c2-98d505f9da63?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Q=
ifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Weekly Dose of Optimism</a><span> t=
o share the stories of the people doing insanely hard things for the benefi=
t of humanity. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Two years later, the world, or =
at least our little corner of it, feels a whole lot more optimistic. When p=
eople pull off incredible things, the roar of the cheers drowns out the sna=
rk and the boos. There&#8217;s a sense that every problem is solvable, even=
, and especially, if it&#8217;s going to take a lot of work to solve it.   =
 </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>That spirit was on full display at Reindustria=
lize. Every speaker and panelist talked about the magnitude of the challeng=
e ahead, and each one seemed to relish the struggle. As Dean Ball wrote in =
his </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/62ac5b4e-5454-4f8c-9370=
-396aa77f9415?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Ex=
kRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">re=
flections on the event</a><span>: </span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-le=
ft: 4px solid #0c2427; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin=
-left: 20px;"><em>In the last year, I&#8217;ve sensed a vibe shift&#8230; I=
 associate this vibe shift with an earnest desire to build&#8212;new factor=
ies, new energy sources, new institutions. A recognition that creating new =
things is preferable to arguing over how to redistribute the things we alre=
ady have. A recognition that history is not over.</em></p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; =
margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>I&#8217;ve had trouble finding the right word=
 to describe this shift. Then, at the </span><a href=3D"https://substack.co=
